FIG. 1 is a drawing for explaining an example of a conventional system for paying public utility charges;


FIG. 2 is a block diagram showing an embodiment of a processing system of charge request data according to the present invention;


FIG. 3 is an arrangement example of charge request data;


FIG. 4 shows an arrangement example of a charge transfer detailed file;


FIG. 5 is a drawing for explaining information of a requesting organization and a paying organization;


FIG. 6 is a flow chart showing flow of each file and data prepared from the charge request data;


FIG. 7 represents examples of transfer slips;


FIG. 8 is a flow chart to show flow of overall processing by the processing system for charge request data;


FIG. 9 is a flow chart to explain an example of collating processing to collate the transfer data;


FIG. 10 is a flow chart to explain an example of a processing to prepare transfer slip;


FIG. 11 is a drawing to show flow of processing of the charge request data according to the present invention;


FIG. 12 is a drawing to explain filter processing and matching processing of the request data;


FIG. 13 shows a concrete arrangement example of a filter processing unit;


FIG. 14 shows an arrangement example of an issuing unit of the request data for each day of payment executed at the receipt of the request data;


FIG. 15 shows an arrangement example of data file for payment day management to be used in the issuance of the request data for each day of payment; and


FIG. 16 shows an outline of the system, which comprises a plurality of requesting organizations, financial organizations and paying organizations.
